  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting inclusive education and equal opportunities for migrant and refugee children and adolescents and host communities in Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project &quot;Promoting inclusive education and equal opportunities for migrant and refugee children and adolescents and host communities in Peru&quot; has been designed in the frame of the ECW Multi-Year Resilience Program (MYRP) for Peru, financed by Education Cannot Wait (ECW). UNICEF as grantee, UNESCO, and other allies as sub-grantees, will work together on this project to respond to the needs of the most vulnerable children and adolescents as well as working towards improving the inclusivity and quality of the Peruvian education system to include Venezuelan refugees and migrants. The MYRP is divided into four &quot;packs&quot;, this document focuses on pack number 2, led by UNESCO Lima.</narrative>
  </description>
